A YOUNG MAN NAMED RONALD GREW UP IN A LIBRARY.
HE THOUGHT HE WAS RICH, BUT HIS PARENTS LAUGHED AT HIM OVER THE DINNER TABLE ONE NIGHT.
THERE WAS NO GUM OR ANYTHING EVER ON THE FLOOR OF THE LIBRARY.
THE FLOOR WAS ALWAYS SO CLEAN AND WAXED, EVEN THE TOPS OF THE BOOK CASES WERE WAXED.
RONALD NEVER INVITED HIS FRIENDS OVER THOUGH BECAUSE HE LIVED IN THE LIBRARY.
HOWEVER, RONALD LOVED THAT AT NIGHT HE COULD RUN FREE IN THE LIBRARY AND MAKE AS MUCH NOISE AS POSSIBLE.
IF A QUESTION WAS BOTHERING RONALD IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT, HE WOULD GET UP AND GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY AND READ UNTIL 3AM.
RONALD GAINED A THIRST FOR LEARNING BY DOING THIS.
NO ONE IN HIS FAMILY GRADUATED HIGH SCHOOL OR WENT TO COLLEGE.
RONALD WENT ON TO COLLEGE, AND EVENTUALLY BECAME A PROFESSOR.
RONALD SHOWED HIS FATHER HIS OFFICE WITH "PROFESSOR CLARK" ON THE DOOR.
A YOUNG MIXED RACE BOY WAS AT THE DINNER TABLE, HIS NAME IS RONALD.
HIS FATHER IS WHITE AND MOTHER IS BLACK.
HE WAS HAPPY HIS FAMILY WAS RICH.
